Cunningham in Ayrshire, named in Celtic as <i>Lugūnon</i> ‘fort of Lugus’ (see   Lyon   2).","Scottish: possibly a variant of   Lothian  ."]},{"name":"Leon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Luis, Manuel, Carlos, Pedro, Jesus, Jorge, Francisco, Rafael, Miguel, Raul.","Spanish (<b>León</b>): habitational name from León, a city in northwestern Spain, named with Latin <i>legio</i>, genitive <i>legionis</i> ‘legion’, a division of the Roman army. In Roman times the city was the garrison of the 7th Legion, known as the <i>Legio Gemina</i>. The city's name became shortened from <i>Legion(em)</i> to <i>Leon(em)</i>, and in this form developed an unetymological association with the word for ‘lion’ (Spanish <i>león</i>).","French (<b>Léon</b>) and Spanish (<b>León</b>): from the personal name <i>Léon</i>, <i>León</i>, from Latin <i>leo</i> ‘lion’, or the cognate Greek <i>leōn</i>. The name <i>Leo(n)</i> was borne by numerous early Christian martyrs and thirteen popes."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen Lyon was born in 1485, in Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Christian Lambe. She died in 1508, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1485–1508":"1485–1508","1482–1529":"1482–1529","1508–1591":"1508–1591","1485":"1485","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1591":"1591","1529":"1529","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Farndon, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Farndon, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–1508":"1485–1508","1482–1529":"1482–1529","1508–1591":"1508–1591","1485":"1485","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1591":"1591","1529":"1529","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Farndon, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Farndon, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1485–1508":"1485–1508","1482–1529":"1482–1529","1508–1591":"1508–1591","1485":"1485","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1591":"1591","1529":"1529","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Farndon, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Farndon, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Ellen Lyon est née en 1485, à Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Christian Lambe. Elle est décédée en 1508, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 23 ans."},"de":{"1485–1508":"1485–1508","1482–1529":"1482–1529","1508–1591":"1508–1591","1485":"1485","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1591":"1591","1529":"1529","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Farndon, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Farndon, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary